Global investors  bought a  net 7.71
billion rupees ($139.6 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 3 percent to 799.3 billion rupees, according
to the exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a record 1.6
trillion rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 4.24 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
